defs.docs: A library for acquiring a backtrace at runtime

defs.name: trace
defs.docs:
Inspects the current call-stack, passing all active frames into the closure
 provided to calculate a stack trace.

defs.name: Frame
defs.docs:
A trait representing one frame of a backtrace, yielded to the `trace`
 function of this crate.

defs.name: resolve
defs.docs:
Resolve an address to a symbol, passing the symbol to the specified
 closure.

defs.name: Symbol
defs.docs: A trait representing the resolution of a symbol in a file.

defs.name: SymbolName
defs.docs:
A wrapper around a symbol name to provide ergonomic accessors to the
 demangled name, the raw bytes, the raw string, etc.

defs.name: Backtrace
defs.docs: Representation of an owned and self-contained backtrace.

defs.name: BacktraceFrame
defs.docs: Captured version of a frame in a backtrace.

defs.name: BacktraceSymbol
defs.docs: Captured version of a symbol in a backtrace.
